Package: parcimonie
Version: 0.11.0-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Debian Privacy Tools Maintainers <pkg-privacy-maintainers@lists.alioth.debian.org>
Installed-Size: 136
Depends: perl (>= 5.20), dirmngr, gnupg (>= 2.1~), libclone-perl, libconfig-general-perl, libfile-homedir-perl, libfile-which-perl, libgnupg-interface-perl (>= 0.52-3), libipc-system-simple-perl, liblist-moreutils-perl, libmoo-perl (>= 1.003001), libmoox-late-perl, libmoox-options-perl, libmoox-strictconstructor-perl, libnamespace-clean-perl, libpath-tiny-perl, libtime-duration-parse-perl, libtry-tiny-perl, libtypes-path-tiny-perl, libtype-tiny-perl, torsocks
Recommends: libglib-perl, libgtk3-perl (>= 0.011), liblocale-gettext-perl, libnet-dbus-perl, libnet-dbus-glib-perl, libpango-perl, libtime-duration-perl, tor
Section: net
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://gaffer.ptitcanardnoir.org/intrigeri/code/parcimonie/
Description: privacy-friendly helper to refresh a GnuPG keyring
 parcimonie is a daemon that slowly refreshes a gpg public keyring
 from a keyserver.
 .
 Its refreshes one OpenPGP key at a time; between every key update,
 parcimonie sleeps a random amount of time, long enough for the
 previously used Tor circuit to expire.
 .
 This process is meant to make it hard for an attacker to correlate
 the multiple performed key update operations.
 .
 See the included design document to learn more about the threat
 and risk models parcimonie attempts to help coping with.
 .
 parcimonie also ships a deprecated desktop applet that allows one
 to monitor the background daemon's activities with a graphical
 user interface. It may or may not work for you, depending on
 your desktop environment.
